rustdoc-ui", "name": "A-rustdoc-ui", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: rustdoc UI (generated HTML)"}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2022-06-18T14:17:06Z", "updated_at": "2022-06-19T22:47:22Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "rustdoc renders labels like \"Deprecated\" next to items like functions which is very useful. However, it sometimes places it ambiguously below an item where you're not sure if it refers to the above item or the below item.\r\n\r\n[See here](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/std/env/index.html)\r\n\r\nFor example in the following screenshot it is not sure whether `std::env::home_dir` is deprecated or `std::env::join_paths`.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17109887/174442274-3b009944-bcef-4210-9629-64ff48f998c0.png)\r\n\r\nI get the same behaviour in both Firefox 101.0.1 and Chrome 102.0.5005.115. I'm on macOS.\r\n\r\nInterestingly the column overflow behaviour for small screens and mobile is much better. For example\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17109887/174442396-c02776c0-6697-43a8-a547-16226e6cdf37.png)\r\n\r\n@rustbot label +A-rustdoc-ui +T-rustdoc ", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/98231/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 1, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/98231/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}